10/12/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A US military delegation led by the Undersecretary of Defence Douglas Feith arrives in Sofia on Wednesday (10 December) to select possible sites for relocation of military bases to the country. The delegation will tour venues and meet with senior officials including President Georgi Parvanov. The Americans visited Romania for similar review Tuesday.
In other news, diplomats from the United States and Britain are urging Bulgaria to demonstrate more political will to battle organised crime. The deputy chief of Britain's diplomatic mission to Bulgaria, Laurence Broyd echoed comments by US Ambassador to Bulgaria James Pardew. (Sega, Standart - 10/12/03; BTA, Mediapool, news.bg - 09/12/03)
